      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "IS THAT A BID (4) has not raced for ten months. Looks forward enough for this return after winning in a recent Gawler trial. Sure to prove hard to beat on his return. PHOEBE ONYX NZ (6) was 9 metres away in second at this track over 2230m last start at his first run back from a spell after racing outside the leader at the bell as the odds-on favourite. Taking on a better line-up this time but he has the ability to mix it with them. ALL THE TRIX (3) is in the mix at his first run since finishing fourth over 2230m at this track 12 weeks ago when after leading for most of the race was outrun late. ALDEBARAN DEXTA (5) resumes from a spell following a break of three-and-a-half months. Generally comes to hand very quickly, with three wins from five first-up appearances. Sure to prove hard to beat on his return.",
